article.headline: Jacksonville 82, Lipscomb 65
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Haminn Quaintance scored 19 points and grabbed 10 rebounds before fouling out as Jacksonville beat Lipscomb 82-65 Monday night. Lipscomb (4-8, 1-3 Atlantic Sun Conference) led 12-10 after two free throws by Charlie Jenney with 12:52 left. Nolan McBride answered for Jacksonville (6-4, 1-2) with a 3-pointer, and Riley Didion added two free throws to give the Dolphins a lead they would never relinquish. Jacksonville extend the lead to 12 at the half on another McBride 3-pointer with 3 seconds left, and stretched the lead to as many as 22 in the second half by outrebounding Lipscomb 42-22. Jure Lozancic scored 17 points, McBride finished with 14 and Didion had 11 for Jacksonville. Lipscomb's Chad Hartman scored 16 points, and James Poindexter added 13 points, but shot just 4-of-15 from the field.
